# Cursor markdown table discipline

When you (a Cursor agent) emit a GFM markdown table, the separator row must have the **same number of cells** as the header row. Cursor-flavor sessions in this repo have a documented history of emitting tables with mismatched column counts (e.g. 7-column header with a 4-column separator), which a GFM renderer correctly drops to a `<p>` of literal pipe text rather than a `<table>`.

Before emitting any table:

1. Count the `|` characters in the header row.
2. Confirm the separator row has the same number of `|` characters.
3. Confirm every data row has the same number of `|` characters.

If they don't match, stop and recount. Do not ship the broken table.

This rule applies only to Cursor sessions. Other agent flavors (Claude, Codex, OpenCode) receive guidance via their system prompts; Cursor's CLI has no equivalent surface, so the rule lives here in `.cursor/rules/`.
